result.name: Hungry Elephant

reviews.text: Staffs are able to speak english, comfy environment. The food is good and dessert is okay. Clean and very open inside. Sometime can be very crowded. However , during none peak hour, it's a good place for relaxing your afternoon.

It's a nice restaurant. But quite pricey and waitresses confuses us about their menu. The menu itself is confusing. As you noticed on my photo we had extra croissants which we were not supposed to have ordered. But we paid it anyway. Hope they can improve it to be worth paying a bucks.
Really excellent food quality. Staff is helpful and friendly!

Had some chicken skewers with peanut sauce and papaya salad. First they confused my order. Then they brought only the skewers. The papaya salad didn't look like the picture on the menu at all either. Tasted fine, but mostly lemon juice.

Surprisingly spacious coffee shop in a busy location in Fortress Hill.

Usually, coffee shops in Hong Kong maximise their expensive rental space by squeezing in as many seats as possible. Whereas Hungry Elephant, the opposite is true and makes for a rare find.

There are seats and tables alongside the wall, a large shared table in the centre and other seating by the window that looks out onto the busy Kings Road in Fortress Hill.

Two or three menus with food and drink items, table service and expect to pay HK$38 for a (strong) cappuccino.
